-- Spurs Beat Heat 114-104 to Take 3-2 Series Lead in NBA Finals
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2013-06-17T02:54:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/spurs-beat-heat-114-104-to-take-3-2-series-lead-in-nba-finals.html
The  San Antonio  Spurs defeated the
Miami Heat 114-104 to move within a victory of winning their
fifth National Basketball Association championship.  Manu Ginobili had 24 points and 10 assists to lead the
Spurs, who took a three-games-to-two lead in the best-of-seven
NBA Finals.  Tony Parker  had 26 points and Danny Green added 24
points, including six three-pointers, for the Spurs at AT&T
Center in San Antonio.  The series now shifts to Miami for Game 6 on June 18.  The defending NBA-champion Heat won Games 2 and 4 after
falling behind 1-0 and 2-1 in the series and need another
victory to force a decisive seventh game on June 20 in Miami.
The Heat last lost back-to-back games on Jan. 8 and 10.  LeBron James and  Dwyane Wade  each scored 25 points for
Miami.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  